  "text": "In recent years, convolutional neural networks (CNN) based face recognition approaches have well developed, and some [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] have achieved more than 99% verification accuracy on the LFW dataset utilizing different loss functions respectively. Given the high efficiency of the existing face recognition works, we directly utilize one of these sophisticated solutions and add it to our compression-reconstruction framework. In our work, we use the scheme proposed in Cosface [CITATION_3] . It uses sphere20 as its network structure, and adopts LMCL (Large Margin Cosine Loss) as its loss function. It was pre-trained on CASIA-WebFace dataset, and can achieve an verification accuracy of 99.28% on the LFW dataset.",
